 #!Rtall314 Changing the Size of the Image Window #!N #!N #!N 
Data Explorer lets you specify the exact height and width of 
the image display area in the Image window, in pixels. When 
you change the size of the image display area, the image 
is resized accordingly. #!N #!N To change the width and height 
of the image display: #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*   #!N #!N #!I30 
#!N 1. Click on the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Window Width #!EF field of 
the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   View Control... #!EF dialog box illustrated in  #!Lcamset58,dxall310 f Figure 58  #!EL  . 
#!N #!I30 #!N 2. Type a new value, specified in pixels, 
for the width. Press the enter key. #!N #!I30 #!N 3. 
Repeat steps 1 and 2 for the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Window Height #!EF 
field. #!N #!I0 #!N #!EF #!N #!N #!N To see effect 
of the changes, specify  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Execute #!EF or  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Execute on 
Change #!EF . #!N #!N #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   Next Topic #!EF #!N 
